description:
Manage a team that designs, develops, troubleshoots and debugs software programs for databases, applications, tools, networks etc. As a manager of the software engineering division, you will apply your knowledge of software architecture to manage software development tasks associated with developing, debugging or designing software applications, operating systems and databases according to provided design specifications. Build enhancements within an existing software architecture and occasionally suggest improvements to the architecture. May telecommute. (385.17607)  



Employer will accept a Master's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or related technical field and 3 years of experience in the job offered or in a Software Development Manager-related occupation.  



Position requires:


1. Designing and developing networking protocol software;


2. Diameter, Gx, Rx, Sh and Sy;


3. 3GPP and wireless networks;


4. Java;


5. Object oriented programming;


6. Multithreaded applications and inter-process communications;


7. Multiprocessor systems; and


8. Supporting customer issues in a Networking/Telecommunications domain.
